<L>__{exterior warsaw city skyline night}
<A>__{artillery fire. fires glow on the horizon.}
<L>__{interior loft, ruined villa night}
<A>__{szpilman wakes suddenly. he listens. silence but for the distant gunfire. he sees the unopened tin of pickles, stares at it. he opens the trapdoor.}
<L>__{interior back stairs, ruined villa night}
<A>__{szpilman, a shadow, a spectre, creeps down the stairs.}
<L>__{interior kitchen, ruined villa night}
<A>__{szpilman has placed the tin and the weight on a shelf and is engrossed in searching again. he finds a pair of chicken scissors. using the weight, he starts to hammer the point of the scissors into the tin making a perforation round the rim. the tin slips off the shelf and rolls across the floor coming to rest at a pair of highly polished jackboots. szpilman stifles a gasp. on the stairs, in silhouette, gazing down at him, the figure of a german captain, the thumb of one hand caught in his belt above his pistol.}
<C>__{the german captain}
<P>__{(stern)}
<D>__{who the hell are you?}
<A>__{szpilman just stares at him.}
<C>__{the german captain}
<D>__{who are you?}
<A>__{no response.}
<C>__{the german captain}
<D>__{what the hell are you doing?}
<C>__{szpilman}
<P>__{(barely audible, in german)}
<D>__{i was... i was trying to open this tin.}
<C>__{the german captain}
<D>__{where do you live?}
<A>__{no response.}
<C>__{the german captain}
<D>__{what's your work?}
<C>__{szpilman}
<D>__{i am... i was a pianist.}
<C>__{the german captain}
<D>__{a pianist.}
<A>__{he studies szpilman for a moment, then with a nod orders him to follow. szpilman picks up the tin and follows.}
